1
00:00:02,353 --> 00:00:06,902
One of Śrīla Guru Mahārāj’s themes was

2
00:00:06,902 --> 00:00:12,532
‘absolute consideration’ and
‘relative consideration’,

3
00:00:13,414 --> 00:00:20,104
and that always we have 
to factor in these two things.

4
00:00:20,465 --> 00:00:24,720
[Absolute and Relative Considerations]

5
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:29,409
And he mentioned as well 
that Śrīla Saraswatī Ṭhākur

6
00:00:29,409 --> 00:00:33,165
particularly in his final days 
was fond of saying,

7
00:00:33,165 --> 00:00:37,859
“Religion means proper adjustment.”

8
00:00:37,859 --> 00:00:43,729
So adjustment between absolute consideration
and relative consideration.

9
00:00:43,969 --> 00:00:53,589
After Kurukṣetra this one brāhmaṇ 
named Uttanka,

10
00:00:53,589 --> 00:00:59,806
he found Kṛṣṇa and he said,
“You Kṛṣṇa, you are responsible 
 

11
00:00:59,806 --> 00:01:06,121
for all these death and distraction,
for creating so many widows …”

12
00:01:06,132 --> 00:01:10,979
Like alluded to in Bhagavad-gītā
varṇa-saṅkara—

13
00:01:12,619 --> 00:01:18,456
illegitimate children, societies,
all the effects, the negative effects

14
00:01:24,198 --> 00:01:25,345
So Uttanka said,

15
00:01:18,456 --> 00:01:24,198
of war and particularly here
the Kurukṣetra war.

16
00:01:25,345 --> 00:01:29,990
“You Kṛṣṇa, you are responsible
for all of these things.

17
00:01:29,990 --> 00:01:34,474
And therefor I’m going 
to curse you!”
 

18
00:01:34,474 --> 00:01:37,912
And Kṛṣṇa said, 
“Hold that thought. 
 

19
00:01:38,462 --> 00:01:43,882
Before you do that 
consider this:

20
00:01:43,882 --> 00:01:54,428
as a brāhmaṇ, you are situated
in a higher aspect of the saguṇa plane;

21
00:01:54,428 --> 00:01:58,499
saguṇa means with guṇas,
with qualities.

22
00:01:58,499 --> 00:01:59,985
What are those qualities?

23
00:01:59,985 --> 00:02:04,150
tamas, rajas, sattva—
ignorance, passion, goodness.

24
00:02:04,150 --> 00:02:07,767
That’s mundane world.

25
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:14,997
So the brāhmaṇ being 
the highest aspect of the mundane.

26
00:02:17,791 --> 00:02:19,958
It’s a good position.

27
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:23,970
go-brāhmaṇa-hitāya ca
jagad-dhitāya kṛṣṇāya
[Viṣṇu Purāṇa: 1.19.65]

28
00:02:23,970 --> 00:02:27,408
Kṛṣṇa likes the brāhmaṇs.

29
00:02:27,408 --> 00:02:33,938
We are told the brāhmaṇs’ hearts 
are by nature pure.

30
00:02:33,938 --> 00:02:38,179
So it’s a nice 
seating place for Kṛṣṇa.

31
00:02:38,179 --> 00:02:42,888
Still it’s a highest aspect 
of the mundane.

32
00:02:42,888 --> 00:02:46,738
So Kṛṣṇa’s saying,
“You are from that position

33
00:02:46,738 --> 00:02:51,940
by your austerities, your tapasyā,

34
00:02:51,940 --> 00:02:57,326
your adherence to religious principles,

35
00:02:57,326 --> 00:03:01,722
your saṃskārs, 
so much in your favor,

36
00:03:01,722 --> 00:03:09,252
you’ve accumulated this energy

37
00:03:09,508 --> 00:03:17,708
and also in terms of power.
Power over the mundane.

38
00:03:19,570 --> 00:03:21,481
But Kṛṣṇa reminded him,
He said,

39
00:03:21,481 --> 00:03:25,197
“But I’m situated 
at the nirguṇa plane.

40
00:03:25,197 --> 00:03:29,481
So you’re going to curse me 
from the saguṇa plane

41
00:03:29,481 --> 00:03:31,725
and it’s not going 
to have any effect upon me, 
 

42
00:03:31,725 --> 00:03:34,125
because I’m 
in the nirguṇa plane.”

